description:
&lt;p&gt;Here at The Royal Free Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust we are passionate about delivering high quality care to our patients. In order to achieve this we are looking to appoint enthusiastic, motivated and experienced Band 5 registered nurses. In return you will receive high quality specialist experience and support. You will work alongside some of the best talent and have access to excellent career and educational pathways and a preceptorship program that meets the Capital Nurse framework&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Transplantation and Specialist Services Division (TaSS) includes following departments and specialities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Endoscopy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gastroenterology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hepato Biliary (HPB) surgery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hepatology &amp; Liver Transplantation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infectious diseases - including HIV&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Oncology &amp; Haematology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Renal services - including dialysis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nephrology &amp; Renal Transplantation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rheumatology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Urology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that vacancies&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;vary across individual departments.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comprehensive Preceptorship and individually tailored training&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership skills for the talented and aspiring leaders of the future&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal Transfer Scheme&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accommodation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Keep Fit schemes and access to staff gym and swimming pool&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nursery and childcare vouchers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Excellent location close to many attractions with easy and fast links to central London&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please submit ONE application even if you are interested in more than one department as your preferences will be discussed at interview. You may have more than one preference please indicate this in the supporting statement of your application. We will contact you before an Assessment day if your preferred department doesn’t have vacancies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due to social distancing and Covid 19 pressures you will be contacted if successful in shortlisting with further details regarding test (if required) and interview. We will use Skype and similar to conduct testing and interviews. Due to challenging times we are experiencing you may be asked to go to different departments and work under difficult circumstances.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Breda Athan - Ambulatory care services, and Infectious diseases: Tel: 0207 794 0500 bleep 1653 or e-mail: breda.athan@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Elly Baker - Renal &amp; Urology services; Tel: 0207 794 0500 bleep 2888 or e-mail elly.baker@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sara Zulu – Oncology; Tel: 0207 794 0500 bleep 2320 or e-mail: sara.zulu@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
